cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and proposes novel methods for addressing two key problems in skin lesion classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses methods for dealing with class imbalance, which is a common problem in machine learning, suggesting that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with high-resolution image data, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
